				\begin{document}$$I{{\bar{4}}}2d$$\end{document}), related to the zincblende structure type. In the chalcopyrite structure, the c axis is approximately twice as long as compared to the basic zincblende cell, and the deviation of the reduced axial ratio η = c/(2a) from 1 is connected with the so-called tetragonal distortion. (In considerations of CIS and other chalcopyrite-type compounds, the tetragonal distortion defined as 1 − η is frequently used.) When surveying the structural data for CuInSe2, we noticed a considerable scatter of the reported a and c values. One of possible reasons of this scatter is deviation from stoichiometry.

